A Ugandan national was arrested in Malelane in Mpumalanga for unlawfully practising as a medical doctor and Abubakari Kaweesa performed illegal abortions for R700 per client and facing charges of the contravention of the health professional Act 56/1974, the choice on termination pregnancy Act 92/1996 as well as medicine Act 101/1996. Kaweesa was arrested by the Hawks in partnership with the Health Professions Council of South Africa on Tuesday after it was discovered that he was a fake medical doctor. On Wednesday he appeared at the Malelane Magistrateâ€™s Court and the matter is set to return to court on Wednesday pending investigation. Hawks provincial spokesperson Capt Dineo Sekgotodi said the suspect was arrested while in the process of attending to a client in need of pregnancy termination.Meanwhile Provincial health spokesperson Dumisani Malamule said they were glad about the suspects has been arrested and would serve as Meanwhile, Provincial health spokesperson Dumisani Malamule said they were glad about the suspects has been arrested and would serve as a warning to other perpetrators. francen@thenewage.co.za